race.comment: THERE GOES MY HERO (7) caught the eye fresh when bursting through late to finish a close fifth. Was only one-paced second-up but should be peaking now over a track and trip he's tasted success at before. Can give this a big shake. CONNI ISLAND (4) gets in well with the claim and is sure to be giving herself every chance again up on speed. Don't take lightly. FLAMING NAVY (1) built on his second two starts back at Morphettville with a win as favourite over 1700m at this track three weeks ago. Tootell scored on him last time and retains the mount. Deserves following up. RICHE D'AMOUR (5) was a long way back last start but hit the line well to finish fifth. Backs up quickly and will appreciate the rise in trip. Watch for him charging through late.
